g.text: ENSEMBLE METHODS
Categorization
Ensemble learning is a machine learning paradigm where multiple models, called weak learners,
will be trained on the same data (or from the same distribution of data). The idea is to
combine multiple weak learners to overcome their limitations.
Bagging trains a set of independent
weak learners in parallel, having as
a side effect a variance reduction.
Bootstrapping is employed in order to deal
with different portions of the data.
The final prediction will be given by the
average or the majority vote.
Bagging
Boosting
With boosting, each weak learner is not
independent anymore. Each model will be fit
one after the other, providing feedback
about the prediction outcomes.
Each model will give a higher importance to
the bad data points, hence the ones
that are not correctly classified.
This allows to reduce the bias.
Stacking
Stacking picks heterogeneous weak learners,
having different learning paradigms.
The output of each model will be used as
input of a meta-model that can be either
a Machine Learning model or an Artificial
Neural Network.
